  "url": "#",
  "content": "The QRcode App, released on the Apple App Store platform in 2016, was the first iOS application capable of scanning QR codes to connect to Wi-Fi on iOS devices. Its primary purpose is to use QR codes as a medium to simplify complex images, text, or data, leveraging smartphones for convenient transmission and interchange. In addition to URL shortening, transforming URLs, PDF Writer, digital business cards, Wi-Fi credentials, and GEO addresses, the app also allows users to create and print Wi-Fi tent cards and stickers for specific scenarios, particularly in College, Office, coffee and bar, motel and homes hospitality. The app is widely used in Norway and across Europe. It ranks 5th in the 'QRcode' keyword category on the App Store, with over 800,000 users and downloads since its launch in 2016.",
